l_{\infty}
x_n(k)\rightarrow x(k)
n\rightarrow\infty
x_n(k)\in c_0
x(k)\in l_{\infty}
\varepsilon>0
N>0
\parallel x_N(k)-x(k)\parallel_{\infty}:=\sup_{k\in\mathbb{N}}|x_N(k)-x(k)|\leq\varepsilon.
\varepsilon
x(k)\rightarrow0
x(k)\in c_0
f:\ell_\infty \to \mathbb R
x\mapsto \lim\sup |x_n|
c_0= f^{-1}(\lbrace 0\rbrace)
l_0
x\notin l_0
r=\frac12\limsup_{k\to\infty} |x(k)|
\|x-y\|\le r
y\notin l_0
\limsup|y(k)| \ge \limsup_{k\to\infty} |x(k)|-r =r
